-- Allianz to Reorganize Board, Financial Times Deutschland Says
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-04-26T20:05:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/allianz-to-reorganize-board-financial-times-deutschland-says.html
Allianz SE (ALV) , Germany’s biggest
insurer, is reorganizing its management board,  Financial Times
Deutschland  reports, citing unidentified people from the
 insurance industry .  Chief Financial Officer Oliver Baete, responsible for
controlling, reporting, and risk, will take on operating
responsibility for a country in the foreseeable future and may
be succeeded by Dieter Wemmer, the newspaper said. Maximilian Zimmerer is to take over Paul Achleitner’s finance department,
the FTD said.  Stefan Nicola in Berlin at +49-30-70010-6246 or
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
